-- Hungary Stocks: CIG, Gedeon Richter Shares Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-03-26T15:48:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-26/hungary-stocks-otp-cig-pannonia-mol-move-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock index
percent fell 0.2 percent to 19,101.07 as of the close in
Budapest. The following were among the most active equities in
the Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CIG Pannonia Eletbiztosito Nyrt. (PANNONIA HB), a Hungarian
life insurer, declined the most in more than four months. The
shares weakened 6.3 percent to 435 forint, the biggest drop on a
closing basis since November. The slump almost reversed a 6.7
percent rally on March 23.  Gedeon Richter Nyrt. (RICHT)  , Hungary’s biggest
drugmaker, fell 1.3 percent to 38,455.00 forint. The company
proposed paying a 660 forint-per-share dividend from its 2011
profit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
